      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(compact): make /compact command cancelable via abortEmbeddedAgentRun",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\nFixes an issue where `/compact` could not be canceled via `/stop`. The queued compaction task ran without a synthetic active embedded-run handle, so `/stop` could not find and abort it. Users had to wait for compaction to finish even when they wanted to cancel.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\nRegister a synthetic active embedded-run handle inside the queued context-engine compaction task (not at command entry time), scoped to manual compaction when no active run already exists. Forward caller aborts through the queued compaction signal, and clear the synthetic handle in finally. Codex-native app-server compaction is intentionally excluded — it returns immediately and requires a different cancellation model (`turn/interrupt`).\n\n## User Impact\nUsers can now `/stop` a running `/compact` command. The compaction is cancelled and the session state is not corrupted.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Vitest:**\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/compact.hooks.test.ts --run\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  14 passed (14)\n\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/commands-compact.test.ts --run\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  71 passed (71)\n```\n\n**What was not tested:** Live gateway `/compact` + `/stop` round-trip (requires running gateway with compaction workload).",
